Scanning


There are four TCP ports open on the target machine. Performing an aggressive nmap scan shows all application except on port 22 are HTTP

Enumeration

Port 8082: HTTP

Browsing to this application displays the webpage above. After a few seconds, it asked me to create an administrator account. It looks like the application has not been fully setup. I used the details admin:admin1.


The Web-File-Server is an interesting feature. There is a file share /fs/ where I have read-write permissions.

Exploitation + Privilege Escalation & Flag


While searching for the exploit for this application, I came across the public exploit shown above. I used this exploit against the target machine and gained a root shell. The author also uploaded a video on how to use the exploit.


To gain a root shell, I followed the author and launched the exploit. I successfully gained a root shell. There is only one flag to capture.
